ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: FMR1 DNA group
ValueRange: Full Mutation; Mosaicism; Premutation Carrier; Unknown; Normal Range
Notes: Fragile X Full Mutation=Individual has >200 CGG repeats in FMR1 gene. Status confirmed by blood test. This causes the FMR1 gene to shut down production of FMRP. The lack of FMRP causes fragile x syndrome; Fragile X Mosaicism; Fragile X Premutation Carrier= Individual has 55-200 CGG repeats in FMR1 gene. Status confirmed by blood test. He/She carries an unstable mutation of the gene that can expand in future generations; Unknown= Individual at risk for FMR1 mutation; Mutation status unknown; Normal Range=Individual has < 45 CGG repeats in FMR1 gene, which falls into the normal range. Status confirmed by blood test. Individual is related to someone with CGG repeat length >55 in FMR1 gene.

ElementDescription: Phenotype/diagnosis for the subject
Family Pedigree User-Defined ID
Enrollment diagnostic group of subject
Notes: FX=Individual has >200 CGG repeats in FMR1 gene. Status confirmed by blood test. This causes the FMR1 gene to shut down production of FMRP. The lack of FMRP causes fragile x syndrome.CX=Individual has 55-200 CGG repeats in FMR1 gene. Status confirmed by blood test. He/She carries an unstable mutation of the gene that can expand in future generations.UX=Individual at risk for FMR1 mutation; Mutation status unknown.TX=Individual has < 45 CGG repeats in FMR1 gene, which falls into the normal range. Status confirmed by blood test. Individual is related to someone with CGG repeat length >55 in FMR1 gene

ElementDescription: Enrollment diagnostic group of family
Race of study subject
ValueRange: American Indian/Alaska Native; Asian; Hawaiian or Pacific Islander; Black or African American; White; More than one race; Unknown or not reported; Other Non-White; Other

ElementDescription: Ethnicity of participant
ValueRange: Hispanic or Latino; Not Hispanic or Latino; Unknown

ElementDescription: Household income range of adult subject
Highest level of education completed for adult subject
Notes: 1 = Grades 1 to 11; 2 = High school graduate or GED; 3 = Associate or technical degree; 4 = Bachelor's degree; 5 = Master's degree; 6 = Doctorate or equivalent professional degree; 9 = Unknown

ElementDescription: Marital status of adult subject
Notes: 1 = Married; 2 = Divorced; 3 = Single or never married; 4 = Widow or widower; 5=Remarried; 6=Separated; 7=Not married but living together with partner; 8=Other; 9 = Unknown

ElementDescription: IQ score as defined by the completion of an appropriate assessement
Date that IQ test was given
Name of IQ test given to participant

Notes: 1 = UC Davis; 2 = Stanford; 3 = Rush; 4 = Duke; 5 = UNC; 6 = Colorado; 7 = Johns Hopkins; 8 = Wisconsin; 9 = Indiana; 10 = Other

Handedness
Notes: 1 = Right-handed; 2 = Left-handed; 3 = Ambidextrous; NYE =not yet established; 999 = missing/refused
